{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840611166,"sessionID":"ses_287a71727ffe6CLZUhi8aHH653","part":{"id":"prt_d78593ef1001mddu6jmIBRwoNy","messageID":"msg_d78591f83001GS6HRZr4Zkxxzi","sessionID":"ses_287a71727ffe6CLZUhi8aHH653","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b13e6faadf9841b58f26aca922dc0803","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define shared types, constants, and common utilities for CRD type definitions in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These shared elements provide:\n6: \n7: 1. **Common Type Definitions**: Shared structs used across multiple CRDs (TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType)\n8: 2. **Label/Annotation Constants**: Standard labels and annotations for sandbox resources\n9: 3. **Condition Types**: Standard condition type constants for status reporting\n10: 4. **Validation Helpers**: Shared validation constants and patterns\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: ### In Scope\n15: \n16: | Deliverable | Description |\n17: |-------------|-------------|\n18: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | Shared type definitions (TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType) |\n19: | Label/Annotation constants | Standard labels/annotations for sandbox lifecycle |\n20: | Condition type constants | Standard condition types for status reporting |\n21: | Default value constants | Default timeout/duration constants |\n22: \n23: ### Type Definitions Required\n24: \n25: #### Shared Types (Already Defined)\n26: \n27: - `TargetPort`: Port configuration with pathPrefix, name, port, protocol\n28: - `ProtocolType`: Enum for HTTP/HTTPS\n29: - `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none\n30: \n31: #### Constants to Define\n32: \n33: - **Label Constants**: Sandbox owner labels, runtime type labels\n34: - **Annotation Constants**: Session tracking, authentication annotations\n35: - **Condition Types**: Ready, Available, Progressing, Degraded\n36: - **Default Values**: Session timeout, max session duration defaults\n37: \n38: ### Out of Scope\n39: \n40: - Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n41: - Webhook validation logic\n42: - CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n43: - client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n44: - AgentRuntime CRD (AR-001)\n45: - CodeInterpreter CRD (AR-002)\n46: \n47: ## Impact Analysis\n48: \n49: ### Upstream Dependencies\n50: \n51: | Dependency | Impact |\n52: |------------|--------|\n53: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.Condition type constants |\n54: \n55: ### Downstream Consumers\n56: \n57: | Consumer | Usage |\n58: |----------|-------|\n59: | AR-001 AgentRuntime | Uses TargetPort, ProtocolType |\n60: | AR-002 CodeInterpreter | Uses TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType |\n61: | Workload Manager | Uses label/annotation constants |\n62: | Router | Uses condition type constants for status checks |\n63: \n64: ## Alternatives Considered\n65: \n66: | Alternative | Pros | Cons | Decision |\n67: |-------------|------|------|----------|\n68: | **Inline constants per CRD** | Localized definition | Duplication, inconsistency | Rejected |\n69: | **Separate constants package** | Decoupled constants | Import complexity | Rejected - keep in shared_types.go |\n70: | **Generated constants** | Automated consistency | Over-engineering for S-size | Rejected |\n71: \n72: ## Risks\n73: \n74: | Risk | Mitigation |\n75: |------|------------|\n76: | Constant naming conflicts | Use package prefix pattern |\n77: | Breaking constant changes | Document stability expectations |\n78: | Condition type proliferation | Define minimal set initially |\n79: \n80: ## Implementation Notes\n81: \n82: 1. **Naming Convention**: Use `LabelKey*`, `AnnotationKey*`, `ConditionType*` patterns\n83: 2. **Documentation**: Add godoc comments for all constants\n84: 3. **Location**: All constants in `shared_types.go` for easy discovery\n85: 4. **Stability**: Mark constants with stability expectations\n86: \n87: ## References\n88: \n89: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n90: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n91: - AR-001 Design: `changes/AR-001/design.md`\n92: - AR-002 Design: `changes/AR-002/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 92 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine shared types, constants, and common utilities for CRD type definitions in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These shared elements provide:\n\n1. **Common Type Definitions**: Shared structs used across multiple CRDs (TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType)\n2. **Label/Annotation Constants**: Standard labels and annotations for sandbox resources\n3. **Condition Types**: Standard condition type constants for status reporting\n4. **Validation Helpers**: Shared validation constants and patterns\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | Shared type definitions (TargetPort, ProtocolType, AuthModeType) |\n| Label/Annotation constants | Standard labels/annotations for sandbox lifecycle |\n| Condition type constants | Standard condition types for status reporting |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775840611145,"end":1775840611165}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840611168,"sessionID":"ses_287a71727ffe6CLZUhi8aHH653","part":{"id":"prt_d78594337001aDDfmSPfVV5o8e","messageID":"msg_d78591f83001GS6HRZr4Zkxxzi","sessionID":"ses_287a71727ffe6CLZUhi8aHH653","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-136b159c340f4a8f8058e1e4b0bfdacb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量\n2: \n3: ## Metadata\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/apis` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-0 |\n12: \n13: ## Scope\n14: \n15: 定义 CRD 共享类型和常量，包括:\n16: - `TargetPort` 类型（端口配置）\n17: - `ProtocolType` 枚举（HTTP/HTTPS）\n18: - `AuthModeType` 枚举（picod/none）\n19: - Label/Annotation 常量\n20: - Condition Type 常量\n21: - 默认值常量\n22: \n23: ## Out of Scope\n24: \n25: - Controller 实现\n26: - Webhook 验证逻辑\n27: - CRD YAML 生成\n28: - client-go 代码生成\n29: \n30: ## Dependencies\n31: \n32: 无外部依赖，为 AR-001、AR-002 提供共享类型。\n33: \n34: ## Deliverables\n35: \n36: | File | Description |\n37: |------|-------------|\n38: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go` | 共享类型和常量定义 |\n39: \n40: ## Acceptance Criteria\n41: \n42: - [ ] 共享类型定义符合 Kubernetes API conventions\n43: - [ ] 常量命名遵循统一命名规范\n44: - [ ] 包含完整的 godoc 注释\n45: - [ ] 通过 `go vet` 和 `golangci-lint`\n46: - [ ] Enum 验证标记正确\n47: \n48: ## References\n49: \n50: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n51: - AR-001 Design: `changes/AR-001/design.md`\n52: - AR-002 Design: `changes/AR-002/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 52 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量\n\n## Metadata\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 |\n| Module | `pkg/apis` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-0 |\n\n## Scope\n\n定义 CRD 共享类型和常量，包括:\n- `TargetPort` 类型（端口配置）\n- `ProtocolType` 枚举（HTTP/HTTPS）\n- `AuthModeType` 枚举（picod/none）\n- Label/Annotation 常量\n- Condition Type 常量","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/spec.md","time":{"start":1775840611148,"end":1775840611167}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840611170,"sessionID":"ses_287a71727ffe6CLZUhi8aHH653","part":{"id":"prt_d785946fc0016AIAdXi9LoPKOr","messageID":"msg_d78591f83001GS6HRZr4Zkxxzi","sessionID":"ses_287a71727ffe6CLZUhi8aHH653","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-1141e5f6f6f244feae96a3f95a03cf77","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: | Item | Value |\n6: |------|-------|\n7: | AR | AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 |\n8: | Module | `pkg/apis` |\n9: | Language | Go |\n10: | Size | S |\n11: | Stage | ST-1 |\n12: \n13: 定义 CRD 共享类型和常量，供 AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter CRD 使用。API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`。\n14: \n15: ## Design\n16: \n17: <!-- TODO: Fill in design details at Stage ST-1 -->\n18: \n19: ### Architecture\n20: \n21: 共享类型和常量定义遵循 Kubernetes API conventions：\n22: - 类型定义使用 `kubebuilder` markers 生成 OpenAPI schema\n23: - 常量使用统一命名规范（LabelKey*, AnnotationKey*, ConditionType*）\n24: - 默认值常量供 controller 使用\n25: \n26: ### Dependencies\n27: \n28: | Package | Purpose |\n29: |---------|---------|\n30: | (无外部依赖) | 共享类型为基础定义 |\n31: \n32: ### Controller-gen Markers\n33: \n34: | Marker | Applied to | Purpose |\n35: |--------|------------|---------|\n36: | `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum` | ProtocolType, AuthModeType | 枚举验证 |\n37: | `+kubebuilder:default` | TargetPort.Protocol | 默认值 |\n38: \n39: ## Data Structures\n40: \n41: <!-- TODO: Fill in data structure details at Stage ST-1 -->\n42: \n43: ### Shared Types\n44: \n45: ```go\n46: // ProtocolType defines the protocol for a target port.\n47: type ProtocolType string\n48: \n49: const (\n50:     ProtocolTypeHTTP  ProtocolType = \"HTTP\"\n51:     ProtocolTypeHTTPS ProtocolType = \"HTTPS\"\n52: )\n53: \n54: // AuthModeType defines the authentication mode for a CodeInterpreter.\n55: type AuthModeType string\n56: \n57: const (\n58:     AuthModePicoD AuthModeType = \"picod\"\n59:     AuthModeNone  AuthModeType = \"none\"\n60: )\n61: \n62: // TargetPort defines a network port configuration for exposing sandbox services.\n63: type TargetPort struct {\n64:     PathPrefix string `json:\"pathPrefix,omitempty\"`\n65:     Name       string `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n66:     Port       uint32 `json:\"port\"`\n67:     Protocol   ProtocolType `json:\"protocol\"`\n68: }\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ### Constants (To Be Defined)\n72: \n73: <!-- TODO: Define specific constants at Stage ST-1 -->\n74: \n75: - Label Constants\n76: - Annotation Constants\n77: - Condition Type Constants\n78: - Default Value Constants\n79: \n80: ## Testing Strategy\n81: \n82: <!-- TODO: Fill in testing strategy at Stage ST-1 -->\n83: \n84: ## File Structure\n85: \n86: ```\n87: pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/\n88:   shared_types.go — 共享类型、枚举、常量\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ## References\n92: \n93: - Source: `/tmp/agentcube-ref/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n94: - AR-001 Design: `changes/AR-001/design.md`\n95: - AR-002 Design: `changes/AR-002/design.md`\n\n(End of file - total 95 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量 |\n| Module | `pkg/apis` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\n定义 CRD 共享类型和常量，供 AgentRuntime 和 CodeInterpreter CRD 使用。API group: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`。\n\n## Design\n\n<!-- TODO: Fill in design details at Stage ST-1 -->\n\n### Architecture\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-003/design.md","time":{"start":1775840611150,"end":1775840611169}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840611173,"sessionID":"ses_287a71727ffe6CLZUhi8aHH653","part":{"id":"prt_d78594b2e0012bmsBM25YiuK5Q","messageID":"msg_d78591f83001GS6HRZr4Zkxxzi","sessionID":"ses_287a71727ffe6CLZUhi8aHH653","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-5e87394bc800476f94f47cf4e60c62d2","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Proposal\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the foundational Go type structures for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These types serve as the core data model for AgentCube's sandbox orchestration platform, enabling:\n6: \n7: 1. **Sandbox Template Definition**: Users define pod templates and runtime parameters via CRDs\n8: 2. **Controller Integration**: The workload manager controller uses these types to create/manage `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` resources\n9: 3. **Client Generation**: These types are the source for `k8s.io/code-generator` to produce typed clients, informers, and listers (see `deployment/client-go.md`)\n10: 4. **Helm Chart CRDs**: `controller-gen` generates CRD YAML from these types (see `manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n11: \n12: ## Scope\n13: \n14: ### In Scope\n15: \n16: | Deliverable | Description |\n17: |-------------|-------------|\n18: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Type definitions for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort, and related structs |\n19: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation with boilerplate |\n20: | `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |\n21: \n22: ### Type Definitions Required\n23: \n24: #### AgentRuntime\n25: \n26: ```\n27: AgentRuntime\n28: ├── Spec\n29: │   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: targetPort)\n30: │   ├── Template (*SandboxTemplate, JSON: podTemplate, required)\n31: │   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, JSON: sessionTimeout, default: 15m)\n32: │   └── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, JSON: maxSessionDuration, default: 8h)\n33: ├── Status\n34: │   └── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition, optional)\n35: └── List: AgentRuntimeList\n36: ```\n37: \n38: #### CodeInterpreter\n39: \n40: ```\n41: CodeInterpreter\n42: ├── Spec\n43: │   ├── Ports ([]TargetPort, JSON: ports)\n44: │   ├── Template (*CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, JSON: template, required)\n45: │   ├── SessionTimeout (*metav1.Duration, default: 15m)\n46: │   ├── MaxSessionDuration (*metav1.Duration, default: 8h)\n47: │   ├── WarmPoolSize (*int32)\n48: │   └── AuthMode (AuthModeType, default: picod, enum: picod|none)\n49: ├── Status\n50: │   ├── Conditions ([]metav1.Condition)\n51: │   └── Ready (*bool)\n52: └── List: CodeInterpreterList\n53: ```\n54: \n55: #### Supporting Types\n56: \n57: - `TargetPort`: Port configuration with optional pathPrefix/name, required port (uint32), protocol (HTTP|HTTPS)\n58: - `ProtocolType`: Enum for HTTP/HTTPS\n59: - `AuthModeType`: Enum for picod/none\n60: - `SandboxTemplate`: Labels, annotations, and embedded `corev1.PodSpec`\n61: - `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`: Image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.\n62: \n63: ### Out of Scope\n64: \n65: - Controller implementation (`pkg/controllers/`)\n66: - Webhook validation logic\n67: - CRD YAML generation (handled by `make gen-crd`)\n68: - client-go code generation (handled by `make gen-client`)\n69: - HTTP API handlers (`pkg/api/`)\n70: \n71: ## Impact Analysis\n72: \n73: ### Upstream Dependencies\n74: \n75: | Dependency | Impact |\n76: |------------|--------|\n77: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required for metav1.ObjectMeta, metav1.Duration, metav1.Condition |\n78: | `k8s.io/api/corev1` | Required for embedded PodSpec in templates |\n79: \n80: ### Downstream Consumers\n81: \n82: | Consumer | Usage |\n83: |----------|-------|\n84: | `make gen-crd` | Generates CRD YAML to `manifests/charts/base/crds/` |\n85: | `make gen-client` | Generates typed clients, informers, listers to `client-go/` |\n86: | Workload Manager (`cmd/workload-manager`) | Reads CRD specs to create Sandbox/SandboxClaim |\n87: | Router (`cmd/router`) | May reference CRD types for routing logic |\n88: | E2E Tests | Validates CRD creation and behavior |\n89: | Helm Chart | Ships generated CRD YAML for installation |\n90: \n91: ### Breaking Change Considerations\n92: \n93: - **Version Stability**: Using `v1alpha1` signals API instability; changes may break existing workloads\n94: - **Field Defaults**: Kubebuilder markers set defaults at CRD level; changing defaults affects existing unlabeled resources\n95: - **Enum Values**: Adding/removing enum values (ProtocolType, AuthModeType) requires CRD schema update\n96: \n97: ## Alternatives Considered\n98: \n99: ### Alternative 1: Use Unstructured CRDs\n100: \n101: **Approach**: Define CRDs via raw YAML without Go types, consume via `dynamic.Client`.\n102: \n103: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n104: |--------|------------|\n105: | Pros | No code generation dependency; faster initial setup |\n106: | Cons | No type safety; no informer/lister generation; harder validation; no IDE support |\n107: \n108: **Decision**: Rejected. AgentCube requires typed clients for controller-runtime integration and test reliability.\n109: \n110: ### Alternative 2: Single Unified CRD\n111: \n112: **Approach**: Merge AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter into one CRD with a `type` discriminator field.\n113: \n114: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n115: |--------|------------|\n116: | Pros | Fewer CRDs; simpler client-go generation |\n117: | Cons | Schema complexity; divergent status fields (`ready` only for CodeInterpreter); authMode only applies to CodeInterpreter; warmPoolSize only for CodeInterpreter |\n118: \n119: **Decision**: Rejected. The two CRDs serve distinct use cases with sufficiently different spec structures.\n120: \n121: ### Alternative 3: External Template Reference\n122: \n123: **Approach**: Use `TemplateRef` (name/namespace) instead of embedded template.\n124: \n125: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n126: |--------|------------|\n127: | Pros | Reusable templates; smaller CRD instances |\n128: | Cons | Additional lookup step; template lifecycle complexity; no inline customization |\n129: \n130: **Decision**: Rejected for initial implementation. Inline templates match agent-sandbox conventions and simplify the user experience. May consider as future extension.\n131: \n132: ### Alternative 4: Duration as int64 seconds\n133: \n134: **Approach**: Use `int64` for timeout/duration fields instead of `metav1.Duration`.\n135: \n136: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n137: |--------|------------|\n138: | Pros | Simpler serialization; no string parsing |\n139: | Cons | Non-standard K8s API; human readability reduced (e.g., \"8h\" vs 28800) |\n140: \n141: **Decision**: Rejected. `metav1.Duration` follows Kubernetes API conventions and provides human-readable defaults (\"15m\", \"8h\").\n142: \n143: ## Risks\n144: \n145: | Risk | Mitigation |\n146: |------|------------|\n147: | Kubebuilder marker typos | Run `make gen-crd` and verify output YAML |\n148: | Missing JSON tags | Use `golangci-lint` with tag-related rules |\n149: | PodSpec embedding complexity | Follow `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` patterns |\n150: | Code-generator version mismatch | Pin `k8s.io/code-generator` v0.34.1 per `hack/update-codegen.sh` |\n151: \n152: ## Implementation Notes\n153: \n154: 1. **Boilerplate**: Use `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` header via `make gen-copyright`\n155: 2. **JSON Tags**: camelCase per project conventions (e.g., `targetPort`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`)\n156: 3. **Kubebuilder Markers**: Apply `+kubebuilder:object:root`, `+kubebuilder:subresource:status`, `+kubebuilder:default`, `+kubebuilder:validation:Required`, `+kubebuilder:validation:Enum`\n157: 4. **Printer Columns**: Add `+kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=\"date\",JSONPath=\".metadata.creationTimestamp\"` for `Age` column\n158: \n159: ## References\n160: \n161: - Kubernetes API Conventions: https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md\n162: - Kubebuilder Book: https://book.kubebuilder.io/\n163: - agent-sandbox API: https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox\n164: - Spec: `changes/AR-001/spec.md`\n165: - Client-go reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 165 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Proposal\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the foundational Go type structures for `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs in the `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1` package. These types serve as the core data model for AgentCube's sandbox orchestration platform, enabling:\n\n1. **Sandbox Template Definition**: Users define pod templates and runtime parameters via CRDs\n2. **Controller Integration**: The workload manager controller uses these types to create/manage `Sandbox` and `SandboxClaim` resources\n3. **Client Generation**: These types are the source for `k8s.io/code-generator` to produce typed clients, informers, and listers (see `deployment/client-go.md`)\n4. **Helm Chart CRDs**: `controller-gen` generates CRD YAML from these types (see `manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go` | Type definitions for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, TargetPort, and related structs |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` | Package documentation with boilerplate |\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` | Scheme registration for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775840611152,"end":1775840611171}}}}
